Hey hi hello everyone! Yes i'm still here! 
Sorry for disappearing for a while.. i'v been facing some hard challenges lately that have managed to drive my strength and positivity down hill.. usually i'm able to keep strong and stay positive but it got to the point of not being able to do something about these obstacles (i hit a brick wall basically). I have not felt helpful whatsoever. I'v felt completely useless and hated seeing the ones i love upset. Life can definitely feel like it is against you, making you feel like everyone/everything is out to get you. I still don't understand why it happens to the people who have always been good to others and have worked hard their whole life; gone through some terrible shit yet still they're the ones who cop the worst through life... no, it doesn't seem fair.  But that's how it is. It does not matter if your a good person or a bad person, it can happen to anyone. Instead of feeling sorry for myself any more than i already have; it is time to face reality. This quote says it all. .

"Dearest Fear,  Creativity and I are about to go on a road trip together. I understand you'll be joining us, because you always do. I acknowledge that you believe you have an important job to do in my life, and that you take your job seriously. Apparently your job is to induce complete panic whenever I'm about to do anything interesting - and, may I say, you are superb at your job. So by all means, keep doing your job, if you feel you must. But I will also be doing my job on this road trip, which is to work hard and stay focused. And Creativity will be doing its job, which is to remain stimulating and inspiring. There's plenty of room in this vehicle for all of us, so make yourself at home, but understand this: Creativity and I are the only ones who will be making any decisions along the way. I recognize and respect that you are part of this family, and so I will never exclude you from our activities, but still - your suggestions will never be followed. You're allowed to have a seat, and you're allowed to have a voice, but you are not allowed to have a vote. You're not allowed to touch the road maps; you're not allowed to suggest detours; you're not allowed to fiddle with the temperature. Dude, you're not even allowed to touch the radio. But above all else, my dear old familiar friend, you are absolutely forbidden to drive." -Elizabeth Gilbert, Big Magic

10 ans, 120 mois, 3650 jours, 87 600 heures, 5 256 000 secondes à me sentir mal dans ma peau. 
14 kilos de perdus, 6 de repris, des centaines de kilomètres parcourus en courant, des centaines de poids soulevés à la muscu, des centaines de litres de transpiration. D'immenses moments de solitude à me trouver grosse, flasque, pleine de cellulite. 
J'ai décidé d'arrêter de n'être qu'un corps. J'ai décidé d'être libre. Libre de pouvoir manger mes foutues graines quand j'en ai envie Et ma foutue pizza le jour d'après. Libre de faire les sports dont j'ai envie, libre de trop donner, libre de ne plus rien devoir à personne, libre de ne plus écouter ce qui me disent que je devrais faire si ou Ca pour perdre encore un peu Parce que Ca va être l'été et que je suis trop rondouillette. Libre de rentrer dans mes jeans 34 et ceux en 38. Libre de porter ce que j'ai envie de porter enfait. Libre de poster mon ventre pas fit ici. Libre d'écouter que les conseils de @lucilewoodward et pas des autres Parce qu'avec ses programmes je me sens libre. Libre de dire au gens que je les aimes parce que le mensonge et la violence ne résolvent rien. Libre de pouvoir revivre mes passions à fond. Libre enfait de ce monde qui m'avait emprisonné dans mon corps, alors qu'on fait une super équipe de sportif. Amélie, 1m62, 64 kilos. Libre de vivre ✌🏻 @mathieu.arnld c'est à toi que je dois cette prise de conscience énorme et tu sais pourquoi !

Jeg faldt over billedet til højre. Jeg ved ærlig talt ikke om jeg skal grine eller græde. På den ene side er jeg enormt chokeret over, hvor langt jeg kunne trække mig selv ud, hvor langt fra den normale Maja jeg kunne blive og hvor usund jeg kunne gøre mig selv, når jeg samtidig godt vidste, at det jeg havde gang i var virkelig skidt. Jeg skammer mig til en vis grad over, at jeg gik rundt sådan der og påførte mine nærmeste den sorg og forvirring, der følger med det at være pårørende til en, der var så syg som jeg. -
Samtidig ynder jeg også at se tingene positivt. Der er trods alt mindre end halvandet år imellem de to billeder, og hvis man samtidig ser på, hvor meget jeg har lært i den tid, er det ret fantastisk. Psykisk, fysisk, fagligt, socialt, personligt og medmenneskeligt er jeg blevet mange gange stærkere, gladere, sundere og ikke mindst klogere. Jeg ser fremad mod den tid der venter mig, alle de oplevelser, der følger med og glæder mig til at se hvad der sker.
